                     Indian River Memorial Amphitheater
   [green_white_right.gif]

   [ext.jpg] Phone: (561) 462-1538
             Fax: (561) 462-1526
             Coordinator: A.W. Cappar [int.jpg]

   The Indian River Memorial Park Amphitheater is located along the Indian
   River Lagoon in downtown Ft. Pierce, Florida.  This open air venue
   hosts music events, religious services and civic events.  It is
   surrounded by several other public facilities such as the Fort Pierce
   Community Center, the A.E. Backus Gallery, the House of the Seven
   Gables, Manatee Observation and Education Center and the Ft. Pierce
   City Marina.  This unique property also houses a mural depicting the
   various periods of growth in St. Lucie County.     Seating capacity is
   2,500.

                                 DIRECTIONS
   From Florida Turnpike (EXIT 152/Fort Pierce Exit) or I-95 (EXIT 65),
   State Rd 68 (Orange Avenue), East to Indian River Drive, North thru
   "round about" to 600 North Indian Drive next to Backus Art Gallery.

   For information on booking, rates, etc., call the St. Lucie County
   Civic Center, (561) 462-1538 or click here cappara@stlucieco.gov
